---
import VizPlaceholder from '../../VizPlaceholder.astro';
---

<section id="multiplayer" class="px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h2
        class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-50 sm:text-4xl"
      >
        And real work is multiplayer
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 grid items-center gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="lg:order-last">
        <div class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-300">
          <p>
            That was one person's day. Now zoom out. Your teammates run their
            own sessions against the same systems, all day, every day. Each
            session solves problems, rules out approaches, encodes decisions.
            And each one stays where it was born:
            <mark>local to one machine, invisible to everyone else</mark>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Someone on your team has almost certainly already worked through
            the exact area you are about to touch. You will never know. Their
            agent learned nothing from yours, and yours learns nothing from
            theirs. The organization runs hundreds of sessions and accumulates
            nothing.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <VizPlaceholder
          label="IsolatedSessions island: many teammates' session nodes appearing across the org, each staying an island, no edges"
          ratio="aspect-[4/3]"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="focus" class="px-6 pb-24 md:pb-32">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl border-y border-neutral-800 py-12 text-center">
    <p class="text-2xl font-medium leading-snug text-neutral-100 sm:text-3xl">
      None of this is the harness's fault.
    </p>
    <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-400">
      Harnesses concentrate on the core: turning a model into an agent that can
      act, and they should. Cross-repo work, provisioning, and shared memory
      are workflow problems one level up, and they need a layer of their own.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
